parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to suddenly accelerate or decelerate, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a loud "helicopter" or "whirring" sound
the vehicle accelerates or decelerates suddenly
the vehicle is stuck in first gear
the vehicle will not shift out of first gear

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to suddenly accelerate or decelerate, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle surges or hesitates while accelerating
the throttle control/transmission warning light illuminates
the vehicle accelerates or decelerates suddenly

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping or Failure to Shift
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to shift properly can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle slips or hesitates while shifting
the vehicle is stuck in first gear
and the vehicle will not shift out of first gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration/lurching forward can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle is in close proximity to pedestrians, other vehicles, or obstacles.
symptoms: The vehicle surges or lunges forward without warning
sometimes when the brake pedal is depressed
stalling or shutting off the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to lunge or surge forward or backward, even when the brake pedal is applied, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle lunges or surges forward or backward
the check engine light and wrench symbol illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk, hesitate, or stall, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, which can lead to engine damage or failure.
The failure of the air conditioning system can cause the vehicle to lunge or surge forward or backward, even when the brake pedal is applied, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The air conditioning system fails to cool
the vehicle lunges or surges forward or backward
